WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:13.344
If you trade prop accounts, this is the most important lab
on the whole dashboard. It answers one brutal question.
Will this setup pass the evaluation, or blow the account
trying?

2
00:00:13.944 --> 00:00:28.632
It's the Prop Simulator, in Step three. It replays your
move thousands of times against a real firm's rules. Your
profit target, your drawdown limit, the daily loss cap,
the minimum days. And it counts how often you pass, versus
how often you bust out.

3
00:00:29.232 --> 00:00:46.104
The most important setting is one most beginners get
wrong. Trailing versus static drawdown. Trailing follows
your highest balance upward, so even giving back profit
can bust you. Static only measures from your starting
balance. Trailing is always harsher, and it's the classic
funded-account rule.

4
00:00:46.704 --> 00:01:04.872
Then you read the three outcomes. Pass Rate is the share
of attempts that hit the target before busting. Above
sixty percent, and the move clears these rules
comfortably. Bust Rate is how often you failed, and it
even splits the reason, drawdown or daily loss. If daily
busts dominate, your size is too big for the rule.

5
00:01:05.472 --> 00:01:21.144
Days to Pass tells you how long a passing run typically
takes, so you can budget the evaluation. And Expected
dollars End is the average ending balance across every
single attempt, pass and bust together. A high pass rate
still has a low expected end if the busts are expensive.

6
00:01:21.744 --> 00:01:34.176
This is where your percentage edge finally meets a prop
firm's actual rulebook. It turns I think this works into
this passes sixty eight percent of the time in about nine
days. That is the entire difference between hoping and
knowing.

7
00:01:34.776 --> 00:01:39.864
Before you ever buy an evaluation, run it right here, a
thousand times, for free.
